Use the standard library
This is how to even_odd_count of num:
   Remember that n is abs of num
   Remember that s is tostring of n
   Remember that even is 0
   Remember that odd is 0
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this s's length times:
      Remember that c is item i in s
      Remember that d is diff of c and 48
      Remember that r is remainder of d and 2
      When r is 0, then:
         Increase even
      But, if not:
         Increase odd
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   The answer is [even, odd]
